  <worksheets>
    <worksheet name='Avg Profit/RR Map'>
      <layout-options>
        <title>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#ffffff'>AVG Profit and Return rate by State</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </title>
        <caption>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#ffffff'>Color shows average of Profit.  Size shows average of Profit.  The marks are labeled by average of Return(Calculated) and average of Profit.  Details are shown for State.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#ffffff'>This map highlights the profitability of each Superstore location, revealing that Oregon consistently underperforms with an average profit of –$16.74. Coupled with a notably high 45% product return rate, the Oregon location represents a sustained loss center and should be considered for closure to protect overall profitability.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </caption>
      </layout-options>
      <table>
        <view>
          <datasources>
            <datasource caption='Orders+ (Superstore)' name='federated.0zqs1ej1dqhmsv1e2ff710w6i10z' />
